  "body": "The DC stream flag is set in the absence of any other stream flags/response codes: https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc#L504\r\n\r\nWhen a codec exception happens, we immediately reset the stream, setting neither a stream flag or a response code: https://github.com/envoyproxy/envoy/blob/master/source/common/http/conn_manager_impl.cc#L263\r\n\r\nAs a result, protocol errors appear with the DC flag set in the access logs.\r\n\r\nWe've seen Envoy respond with a 400 for some protocol errors at least (in which case the response code should probably be set), but I'm guessing not all protocol errors result in a 400 so we should at least set a stream flag for protocol errors (PE?)",
